data.description: Large and versatile home in Waiakea.  The living room features vaulted ceilings,  a floor to ceiling  lava rock fireplace to warm those chilly nights,  expansive glass windows to showcase the ocean views, and a powder room for convenience.   There is both formal and informal dining areas, showcased by built in Koa cabinetry and lovely stained glass lighting fixtures.  The galley style kitchen has been upgraded with stainless appliances and includes a pantry and  pass through bar top to the dining room.  The main level also includes two bedrooms with access to a full bath and a master bedroom with en-suite full bath.    The  lower level has a second master suite with half bath, hardwood flooring and a separate shower/furo.  The lower level  family room offers ample storage, a great kids hangout, a possible work out room, tv viewing room  or just a great getaway space.  Did I mention there is also a wet bar to compliment your entertaining nature. The bonus room is currently used as an office.   The laundry area on the lower level has newer stainless, front loading machines.  Located on a large corner lot, this property showcases lava rock fencing and a beautifully terraced and landscaped  yard.  It has an amazing array of mature native plantings as well as many fruit trees, such as:  avocado, ulu, lemon, tangerine and more.  The home was reroofed in 2007 and interiorly  painted this year. The faucets in kitchen and baths have been replaced. The home is serviced by photovoltaic panels to help with electric costs. Sellers have an appraisal dated June 19, 2023, substantiating the listing price, which can be shared with a serious buyer.   Don't pass up the opportunity to show this grand gem.   Must see to appreciate.
